page.title: 02Geog & Geol continued....
page.content: ...underlying schist have been eroded by sea and overlying head has been differentially eroded.{The coast to} {Lannacombe}shows similar features with {(i)}Much degraded interglacial cliff at the top of the coastal slope, dropping to{(ii)}a terrace of periglacial head (partly eroded). {(iii)}Partly vegetated cliff cut in head deposits.{(iv)}Much dissected raised shorelines &{(v)}a modern shore platform. {The Skerries} To the west of Start Point the Skerries Bank stretches North Eastwards. This shallow area has led to many shipwrecks and the area is of great interest to sub-aqua divers in the summer.
